---

Types

fix: A bug fix that affects end-users.
feat: A new feature added to the codebase.
build: Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (npm, Gradle, Webpack, etc.).
chore: Routine tasks and maintenance that do not affect production code (cleanup, config updates).
ci: Changes to CI/CD configuration or scripts (GitHub Actions, Jenkins, etc.).
docs: Documentation updates only (README, comments, API docs, wiki).
style: Code style changes that do not affect logic (formatting, spacing, lint fixes).
refactor: Code changes that restructure existing code without altering its external behavior.
perf: Performance improvements that make the code faster or more efficient.
test: Adding, updating, or fixing tests (unit, integration, e2e).
types:

Use <type>! to indicate a breaking change.
`feat!: remove deprecated user API`
